CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 17, 1959, pg. A15, reads: "To Live in Buffalo - Mr. and Mrs. Daniel L. Wilburn were married by the Rev. H. S. Cuff of Corinthian Baptist Church. The bride is the former Mrs. Fannie Mae Nelson.  Attendants were: Mrs. Geraldine Mott, maid-of-honor, Mrs. Vera Ghoston and Johnny Warren, best man.  Mrs. Catherine Kenley directed the wedding. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Groom Daniel Wilburn wearing light colored dinner jacket, and bride Fannie Mae Nelson Wilburn wearing sleeveless dress with diamond pattern and holding bouquet of carnations, posed in interior
